Guinea announces that the second round of voting for the Guinea presidential election will be on October 24 after months of delay. (CNN)The Sudanese government fires the special prosecutor for Darfur war crimes, in what the Sudan Tribune calls "an apparent bid to deflect the case of the International Criminal Court against President Omar al-Bashir". (Sudan Tribune)The Obama administration notifies the United States Congress of plans for a $60billion-dollar weapons deal with Saudi Arabia in a move to threaten Iran. (CNN) (Reuters)